A 61-year-old man, who did not have a mask on and was cutting plants illegally, turned aggressive towards NParks officers who had approached him, and attacked one of them with a sharp instrument.
The safe distancing enforcement officer from NParks was putting up SafeEntry signs along the Sungei Serangoon Park Connector.
He sustained serious injuries to his chest, arm and hand.
Link in bio @straits_times
📸: Singapore Police Force
#coronavirus #covid19 #StraitsTimes

The safe distancing enforcement officer from NParks was putting up SafeEntry signs along the Sungei Serangoon Park Connector.
He sustained serious injuries to his chest, arm and hand.
Link in bio @straits_times
📸: Singapore Police Force
#coronavirus #covid19 #StraitsTimes
